SEVEN cops have been dismissed in connection with involvement in corruption. Police spokesman Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said on Tuesday, 1 December police management fired seven senior managers. They include two brigadiers, a colonel, two lieutenants-colonel and two ordinary employees. They are: Said Naidoo: “The seven were among 16 suspects initially arrested on 4 June during a predawn operation.” They’ve been tried internally, found guilty and dismissed.